#. <section class="sutta" id="an6.49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an6.49:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an6.49:0.2"
msgid "5. Dhammikavagga"
msgstr "5. About Dhammika"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an6.49:0.3"
msgid "49. Khemasutta"
msgstr "49. With Khema"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.359"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an6.49:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an6.49:1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā ca khemo āyasmā ca sumano sāvatthiyaṃ "
"viharanti andhavanasmiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time Venerable Khema and Venerable Sumana were staying near "
"Sāvatthī in the Dark Forest."

msgctxt "an6.49:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ca khemo āyasmā ca sumano yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho āyasmā khemo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then they went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. Venerable "
"Khema said to the Buddha:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an6.49:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Yo so, bhante, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto tassa na evaṃ "
"hoti:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed "
"the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, "
"achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is "
"rightly freed through enlightenment—does not think:"

msgctxt "an6.49:2.2"
msgid "‘atthi me seyyoti vā atthi me sadisoti vā atthi me hīnoti vā’”ti."
msgstr "‘There is someone better than me, or equal to me, or worse than me.’”"

msgctxt "an6.49:2.3"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā khemo."
msgstr "This is what Khema said,"

msgctxt "an6.49:2.4"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "an6.49:2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā khemo “samanuñño me satthā”ti uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then Khema, knowing that the teacher approved, got up from his seat, bowed, "
"and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an6.49:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sumano acirapakkante āyasmante kheme bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "And then, not long after Khema had left, Sumana said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an6.49:3.2"
msgid ""
"“yo so, bhante, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo vusitavā katakaraṇīyo ohitabhāro "
"anuppattasadattho parikkhīṇabhavasaṃyojano sammadaññāvimutto tassa na evaṃ "
"hoti:"
msgstr ""
"“Sir, a mendicant who is perfected—with defilements ended, who has completed "
"the spiritual journey, done what had to be done, laid down the burden, "
"achieved their own true goal, utterly ended the fetters of rebirth, and is "
"rightly freed through enlightenment—does not think:"

msgctxt "an6.49:3.3"
msgid "‘natthi me seyyoti vā natthi me sadisoti vā natthi me hīnoti vā’”ti."
msgstr "‘There is someone better than me, or equal to me, or worse than me.’”"

msgctxt "an6.49:3.4"
msgid "Idamavocāyasmā sumano."
msgstr "This is what Sumana said,"

msgctxt "an6.49:3.5"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "an6.49:3.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā sumano “samanuñño me satthā”ti uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi."
msgstr ""
"Then Sumana, knowing that the teacher approved, got up from his seat, bowed, "
"and respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before "
"leaving."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an6.49:4.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā acirapakkantesu āyasmante ca kheme āyasmante ca sumane "
"bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr ""
"And then, soon after Khema and Sumana had left, the Buddha addressed the "
"mendicants:"

msgctxt "an6.49:4.2"
msgid "“evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, kulaputtā aññaṃ byākaronti."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, this is how people from good families declare enlightenment."

msgctxt "an6.49:4.3"
msgid "Attho ca vutto attā ca anupanīto."
msgstr "The goal is spoken of, but the self is not involved."

#. VAR: hasamānakā → hasamānakaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an6.49:4.4"
msgid "Atha ca pana idhekacce moghapurisā hasamānakā maññe aññaṃ byākaronti."
msgstr ""
"But it seems that there are some foolish people here who declare "
"enlightenment as a joke."

msgctxt "an6.49:4.5"
msgid "Te pacchā vighātaṃ āpajjantīti."
msgstr "Later they will fall into anguish."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an6.49:5.1"
msgid "Na ussesu na omesu,"
msgstr "They don’t rank themselves"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nopanīyare → nopaniyyare (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "an6.49:5.2"
msgid "Samatte nopanīyare;"
msgstr "as being higher, or lower, or equal."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.49:5.3"
msgid "Khīṇā jāti vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ,"
msgstr "Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an6.49:5.4"
msgid "Caranti saṃyojanavippamuttā”ti."
msgstr "They live freed from fetters.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an6.49:5.5"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
